### Week 4

---

#### Designing an Icon

Towards the end of week 3, we designed a icon for the game "시장에 가면." Designing a good icon generally takes 4 key things to look at. The icon should be as simple as possible, too complex would make it hard to understand what the app is. There should be a metaphor, a symbol that stands for something in the game so you can recognize it. The icon should be as simple as possible, making it easier to see. There should be some connection to the actual game that it is representing. And the last thing is lineage, icons should be recognizable or grouped with other icons easily, and the design should not change drastically every change.

My first draft is shown in figure 1. I eventually went with a golden shopping cart, the same design as in the game, so that it was familiar to the players. This however was only my first draft
![image](https://res.cloudinary.com/dfyhppahy/image/upload/v1675139260/Screen_Shot_2023-01-30_at_8.21.50_PM_dibfaa.png)
*Figure 1*

Next we learned about the icon grid. Most apps in IOS follow this grid as it makes the icons appear clean and consistent. This can help to identify apps or help them pop out. As shown in the figure, the icon was made in the grid and was placed into the IOS home screen. This is to see if the design is easy to see and stands out from the other apps.

![image](https://res.cloudinary.com/dfyhppahy/image/upload/v1675139261/Screen_Shot_2023-01-30_at_8.20.13_PM_ibiwic.png)
*Figure 2*

Next it was our turn! I liked my design with the cart in the middle but as one of the teachers pointed out, there was no real connection that it was a game centered around memory. So I added a brain as kind of a logo for the cart (figure 3)
![image](https://res.cloudinary.com/dfyhppahy/image/upload/v1675139261/Screen_Shot_2023-01-30_at_8.20.20_PM_ngkwn1.png)
*Figure 3*

My logo in these next figures are pasted into the IOS platform, CallusCompany's app, and other icons that follow the same theme.

![image](https://res.cloudinary.com/dfyhppahy/image/upload/v1675140501/Screen_Shot_2023-01-30_at_8.47.51_PM_ilxbgk.png)
